@@CharToHtml
<TITLE CharToHtml function>
Summary
  Converts a character to a string that can be used in a HTML document.
Description
  CharToHTML converts Ch to a character string that can be used in a HTML document regardless of the
  users locale or Windows version. For example, the character '\<' is converted to the string '&lt;';
Parameters
  Ch - The character to convert
See Also
  HtmlToString, StringToHtml, TJvStrToHtml

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@HtmlToString
<TITLE HtmlToString function>
Summary
  Converts a HTML string to a plain string.
Description
  HtmlToString converts the content of Value into an equivalent plain string. For example, the string
  '&lt;CODE&gt;' is converted into '\<CODE\>'.
Parameters
  Value - The string to convert.
See Also
  CharToHtml, StringToHtml, TJvStrToHtml

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@StringToHtml
<TITLE StringToHtml function>
Converts a plain string to a HTML string.
Description
  StringToHtml converts the content of Value into an equivalent HTML string. For example, the string
  '\<CODE\>' is converted into '&lt;CODE&gt;'.
Parameters
  Value - The string to convert.
See Also
  CharToHtml, HtmlToString, TJvStrToHtml

